    • Field Detail

      • type

        public final int type
        The type of the limiter. One of MediaUtils.TYPE_ARTIST, TYPE_ALBUM, TYPE_GENRE, or TYPE_FILE.

      • names

        public final java.lang.String[] names
        Each element will be given a separate view each representing a higher different limiters. The first element is the broadest limiter, the last the most specific. For example, an album limiter would look like: { "Some Artist", "Some Album" } Or a file limiter: { "sdcard", "Music", "folder" }

      • data

        public final java.lang.Object data
        The data for the limiter. This varies according to the type of the limiter.
